if mibBuilder.loadTexts: docsPnmCmtsUsOfdmaRxMerNumAvgs.setDescription("This attribute controls the number of probes the CMTS will use to calculate the Rx MER per subcarrier. The average will be computed using the 'leaky integrator' method, where reported Rx MER per subcarrier value = alpha*accumulated values + (1-alpha)*current value. Alpha is one minus the reciprocal of the number of averages. For example, if N=25, then alpha = 0.96. A value of 1 indicates no averaging. Re-writing the number of averages will restart the averaging process. If there are no accumulated values, the accumulators are made equal to the first measured bin amplitudes. This object cannot be changed while a capture is in progress. It will return a value of 'inconsistentValue' if set while the value of 'docsPnmCmtsUsOfdmaRxMerMeasStatus' is set to a value of 'busy'. ")
